title: For Sale/Trade:  Colt 1911 Original WWI from 1918, Great Collectible Shooter
location: Havelock, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
I have an original Colt M1911 USGI from WWI that I am looking to trade. This gun shoots amazingly well for being almost 100 years old - nothing less than expected from an original Colt! The serial number on the frame traces to 1918, and the slide with the rear rampant Colt is from 1914 to late 1917. The AA mark on the slide means that it went through an arsenal rebuild at Augusta Arsenal sometime after the war, as did many USGI WWI and WWII firearms. Once there, they parkerized it and swapped out any faulty or damaged parts and put it back into service. Post-war arsenals rebuilds focused more on functional parts and not keeping its original parts for collectibles, a lot of parts were mismatched. I do not know enough about the parts on it, but I do know the grips and the slide stop were replaced with later versions. The mainspring housing is still original to the gun. The gun likely received the Coltwood grips at Augusta as well. It is what would many would consider a collectible shooter. 

I fired around 30 rounds through it after I received it and it shoots great and is very accurate. The only "damage" to it is a little off-coloring on the left side, near the muzzle. In my opinion, it does not appear to be rust or pitting, but is likely discoloration of the metal. All in all, it is barely noticeable. Has all correct military markings and nice rifling in the barrel. Both slide and frame lock up great. Pistol includes 2 unmarked 7-round magazines and blue Colt box.

I replaced the springs in it because I did not know when the last time it received and upgrade on the mechanical/operational parts. Like I said, it shoots great and I hate to get rid of it because I love the gun and its history, but want to try something different.

More pictures can be found here:

http://s1337.photobucket.com/user/carsoca2/library/Colt%201911?sort=6&page=1

Please let me know if you are interested. Thanks.

title: For Sale:  Carbine 1 Course - Civilian Carbine Course
postcontent:
Mid-Ohio Personal Defense Solutions is very excited to offer Mid-Ohio’s Only Carbine Course. This course is taught by experienced certified instructors and trainers with many years of experience in the shooting sports. 

Recent events and the legislative response have created an unprecedented demand for AR variant and similar carbines. Many of the purchasers are first time carbine owners with much to learn. The defensive/tactical carbine is unique weapon system with a steep learning curve. If you are a first time AR or carbine owner, or an experienced shooter who would like to take your game to the next level, this course is a must.

The Defensive Carbine Course is designed to provide each student with the core skills needed to properly and effectively utilize an AR based carbine both safely and effective manner in both defensive and sporting applications.

This intense one-day (8-hour) course will include:
•Safety
• History of the AR Platform
• Nomenclature
•Carbine Function and Design
•Operation and Manipulation
•Ammunition Selection
•Ballistics
•Optics and sighting
•Trigger Control
•Proper Shooting Positions
• Precision Shooting to 50 Yards
•Close Quarter Battle Drills
•Malfunctions and Resolutions
•Balancing Speed vs. Accuracy
•Personal / Home Defense Considerations



This course includes 4 hours of practical instruction, followed by 4 hours of practical application and shooting at our shooting range.

This course is primarily designed for the AR platform. However, students are welcomed to bring any other serviceable carbines such as, AK’s Mini-14s, SK/SKS, etc. Please understand that portions of the course may not apply to these specific weapon systems.

Required Equipment:
• Serviceable Carbine
•Minimum 2 Magazines
•Minimum 200 rounds of factory ammunition – NO RELOADS!
•Eye Protection
•Hearing Protection


 This course will be held in Butler, Ohio (near Mansfield, about 1 hour north of Columbus & 1 hour south of Cleveland) and with the shooting drills at our private, multi-level shooting range. Space is limited. Please contact us today!

title: For Sale:  .45-70 Mauser 98 with long glass (Spot-Shot 15x)
postcontent:
She was born in Tokyo, Japan in 1943 as I have been told... This model is called a "Siamese Mauser"... originally chambered in 8x52Rmm. She later grew (1960s I believe) into a sporterized .45-70 Government and took on some glass and a new stock... 

The optic is a Davis Spot-Shot 15x (R.A. Litschert retired in 1961, selling the business to Myron Davis, who continued to manufacture Litschert's quality scopes as the Davis Optical Company. of Winchester, Indiana). I have been told the stock is a Fajen, but do not personally know this to be correct.

She is a truly massive gun with as solid aluminum adjustable buttplate and solid brass buttplate "horn" (and so long indeed that I had to drill a hole in my largest rifle case to accommodate said "horn" (case is optional with sale... $50 extra... very nice case)).

She is an absolute joy to shoot with very very mild recoil.

Three notes:

- She has an EXTREMELY light match/target trigger.

- The three position safety/bolt needs to be polished/honed to return functionality (common problem I am told and will leave this to the buyer who undoubtedly will be a Mauser lover). 

$900 with case $850 without
Fastest response is e-mail  REDACTED

- The scope reset spring is missing. Not critical, but should be replaced.
